Install SSH

1) sudo apt-get install openssh-server

2) Take a copy of the default SSH configuration and rename it as factory default
        => sudo cp /etc/ssh/sshd_config /etc/ssh/sshd_config.factory-defaults

3) Modify it's permissions
        => sudo chmod a-w /etc/ssh/sshd_config.factory-defaults

4) sudo systemctl restart ssh

5) Make a folder => mkdir ~/.ssh

6) Change it's permission : chmod 700 ~/.ssh

7) Connect over LAN : ssh username@ip.address.here


Enable SSH / SCP without entering password 
https://linuxize.com/post/how-to-setup-passwordless-ssh-login/
